HR Staff  -
HR Staff
Responsibilities
Maintains human resources records by recording new hires, transfers, terminations, changes in job classifications, merit increases; tracking vacation, sick, and personal time.Administering payroll and maintaining employee records.Dealing with grievances and implementing disciplinary procedures.Planning, and sometimes delivering, training, including inductions for new staff.Analyzing training needs in conjunction with departmental managers.Liaising with a wide range of people involved in policy areas such as staff performance and health and safety. Requirement : FemaleMax age 28 years oldMin. S1, Graduates from a reputable UniversityWorking experience at least 3 years in H/R , G&A & TrainingProficient in the use of Ms. Office and InternetIndependent and able to work under pressure to meet tight reporting deadline and attention to detail and accuracyAbility to interact with people effectivelyGood command in English (reading, speaking and writing)Attractive, good performance, personality, honest, self motivated, disciplineWilling to be placed in Purwakarta/ Cikampek, West Java  Please send  your application letter complete with CV, recent photograph and expected  to:E-mail: hrdvai@ymail.com (email should not exceed 300 kb)
